EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND ACROSS THE UK DURING THURSDAY EVENING
WITH LOW PRESSURE SITUATED OVER SCANDINAVIA. ANOTHER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
WILL DEVELOP NEAR ICELAND WHICH IS EXP TO DRIFT EWARDS INTO THE NORWEGIAN
SEA FLN IN THE PROCESS OVERNIGHT INTO FRIDAY. HIGH PRESSURE WILL REMAIN SITUATED
